DBIO — Future Features
======================

These items are tracked here until they are moved to the project's
ticket system.

## UNION support

SQL UNION / UNION ALL via ResultSet API. Depends on SQL::Abstract
gaining native UNION support or DBIO wrapping it at the SQLMaker level.

## Row/find caching

ResultSet-level cache for find() and single-row lookups:
  - Configurable cache invalidation strategy
  - Manual invalidation API (single item / table / entire cache)
  - Optional TTL-based expiry
  - Needs clear semantics for when the cache is queried vs bypassed

## Auto-discover joins

Automatically detect required joins from search condition keys:
  $rs->search({ 'author.name' => 'Fred' })
  # should auto-add: join => 'author'
Detection via ResultSource relationship introspection.
Implementation point: ResultSet::_resolved_attrs() before join resolution.

## Inflated objects in search conditions

Auto-deflate inflated column values passed to search():
  $rs->search({ created_at => $datetime_obj })
  # should auto-deflate via column's deflator
Requires extending deflator signature to work without Row object context.
FIXME comment already exists in Storage::DBI::_select_args().
